CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - BULAHDELAH Pacific Hwy at Bulahdelah Bypass
properties.otherAdvice:
The Bulahdelah Bypass is now open to southbound traffic.

Northbound traffic will continue to travel through the town of Bulahdelah for the next four weeks. This will allow work to be completed on the bypass including the installation of noise walls and barriers.

The southbound lanes of the bypass will remain open and the upgrade will open to northbound traffic from the end of July 2013, weather permitting.

properties.headline: CLEARWAYS - SYDNEY CBD Various Roads
properties.otherAdvice:
Railcorp CBD Rail Closure.

Special Event Clearways will be implemented in the following locations from 2am Saturday 13 July until 2am Monday 15 July:
Chalmers Street, Surry Hills - western side between Cleveland Street and Eddy Avenue
York Street, CBD, western side between Margaret Street and Erskine Street
Pitt Street, Haymarket, eastern side between Railway Square and Eddy Avenue.

The taxi zone on the western side of Chalmers Street to the eastern side of Chalmers Street (adjacent to the dental hospital) will also be undertaken.

Please check signage before parking as vehicles will be towed and fines apply.
